# dependencies & build output
node_modules
dist/
.vite/
# the published `spexcode` package (repo root) ships spec-dashboard/dist — covered by the `dist/` rule
# above. It's a prepublishOnly build artifact (publish-time only), never committed (see .../spec-cli/packaging).
# `npm pack` output (the publishable tarball) — a build artifact, never committed
spexcode-*.tgz
# legacy bundled-dist location (pre root-publish); ignore if a stale copy reappears
spec-cli/dashboard-dist/

# SpexCode worktrees live here — they are separate checkouts, never committed
.worktrees/

# per-worktree session runtime — EVERY harness-written artifact under ONE ignored dir (state, prompt,
# launch, hooks.json, launch.sh, claude.md), so the worktree's spec/code tree stays clean. (`.session` with
# no trailing slash also covers a legacy flat `.session` state file.) Removed with the worktree.
.session
# legacy flat runtime sidecars (pre runtime-dir refactor) — still ignored while in-flight sessions drain;
# remove these five lines once no flat-layout worktree remains.
.session-prompt
.session-launch
.session-comms.ndjson
.spex-hooks.json
.spex-launch.sh
CLAUDE.spexhidden.md

# harness state (local settings, transcripts) AND generated sub-agent definitions: .claude/agents/*.md is now
# MATERIALIZED from `surface: agent` source nodes (e.g. spec-scout), per-machine, never committed — so the
# whole dir is ignored, exactly like the skill SKILL.md and the shims (the managed block below lists each).
.claude/*

# machine-local claude binary symlink (points into a per-machine install); the session
# launcher resolves `claude` from PATH (SPEXCODE_CLAUDE_CMD), so this is never vendored
spec-cli/bin/claude

# generated review artifacts at the worktree root — a one-off harness-adapter review report (machine-emitted,
# self-contained HTML, no human curation). The project folder holds only human-readable, curated prose
# (curated HTML docs live under .spec/.../taste/, not the root); a regenerated report stays untracked.
harness-report.html
harness-report-serve

# machine-local config overlay (host-specific values that must NOT be committed — e.g. an absolute
# worker-launcher path); readConfig() layers it over the committed spexcode.json. See portable-layout.
spexcode.local.json

# os / editor
.DS_Store
*.log
HARNESS-REFACTOR-REPORT.md
firecoder-scout.md

# spexcode:start
.claude/agents/spec-scout.md
.claude/settings.json
.claude/skills/taste/SKILL.md
.codex/skills/taste/SKILL.md
AGENTS.md
CLAUDE.md
spexcode.local.json
# spexcode:end
